Above codes are used to bound and find the minima of single variable functions i.e. y = f(x)

Steps to run:

1) Download all files in a single directry on any linux machine
2) Change functions and their derivatives in func.cpp and gfunc.cpp and save
3) Open terminal in the same directory
4) Type: make all
5) This will generates 4 executable files namely: swann, fib, gsec, nraph
6) Run the desired executatble file by typing: ./name (name = fib, gsec ...)

swann - Bounds the minima of a function using Swann's Algorithm (Inputs - start point x, step size delta)
fib - Bounds the minima of the function using Fibonacci's Algorithm (Inputs - start point x, step size delta)
gsec - Finds minima of the function using Golden Section Algorithm (Inputs - lower bound xl, upper bound xu, Accuracy of Minima)
nraph - Finds minima of the function using Newton Raphsons Algoritm on derivatives (Inputs - initial guess x0, Accuracy of minima)

*** Note nraph requires function to be twice differentiable
